Taking DDL away from JPA and giving it to Flyway. (spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create or update)
   - A liability in production
   - Hibernate's schema generation is non-deterministic across versions
   - Doesn't give rollback capability
   - Gives zero audit trail of schema changes
   - The industry standard is ddl-auto=validate (Hibernate checks that entities match the schema but touches nothing) with Flyway owning all DDL
   - Spring Boot + Flyway auto-discovers classpath:db/migration by default, so no extra config needed


AuthMat Security Filter
    - AuthMat is the identity provider. It has endpoints that the gateway calls directly (/auth/login,
      /auth/refresh, /jwks). It has internal admin endpoints. It may receive service-to-service calls
      that never go through the gateway at all.